Version- 0.1
Author- Aaditya Bagga <aaditya_gnulinux@zoho.com>
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
slacker acts like a package manager for your local copy of slackbuilds.
(usually obtained from slackbuilds.org)

It supports following functions/options:

1) search the repository (-s)
2) info about specified package (-i)
3) readme about specified package (-r)
4) goto the package directory (-g)
5) view slackbuild (-v)
6) list files contained in specified package directory (-l)
7) description about specified package (-d)
8) get/download the package (-G)
9) build the package (-B)
10) install the built package (-I)
11) upgrade installed package with built package (-U)
12) remove installed package (-R)
13) query installed packages (-q)
14) view all packages in the slackbuilds repo (-a)
15) update git repo of slackbuilds (-u)

It uses the following (Slackware) tools:

1) installpkg
2) removepkg
3) upgradepkg

The variables used are:

1) repo=""
 # Repository for slackbuilds"

2) terminal="" 
 # Terminal used for going to the package

3) srcpath=""
 # Where the downloaded source packages are to be placed.
 # Leave it blank for saving in the same directory as the slackbuild.

4) outpath=""
 # Where the build package will be placed. 
 # Leave it blank for putting them in /tmp.

5) gitdir=""
 # Directory where slackbuilds git repository is stored

Samples for these variables are present in the script itself.

Installation:
(as root)
make install

Usage:
slacker <option> [package]

Examples:
slacker -s dosbox (search for package dosbox)
slacker -i dosbox (read the info file for dosbox)
slacker -v dosbox (view slackbuild)
slacker -G dosbox (get(download) dosbox(source))
slacker -B dosbox (build package for dosbox)
slacker -I dosbox (install built package)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
